'He was too late [coming back for pre-season],' added Koeman. 'The decision of the board was to allow him not to come back. We have to look for opportunities for him to play in a different team.'

The Italian scored three times in 13 Premier League appearances, including a fine curling strike against Manchester City at the Etihad in December.

But he was shipped out on loan to Juventus in January after being suspended for three matches and fined £40,000 for violent conduct during an incident at Newcastle, and then being involved in an altercation with team-mate Fonte on the training ground.

