Meanwhile, Koeman insists no bids have been accepted for defender Dejan Lovren, who is a summer target of Brendan Rodgers at Liverpool.

Despite this the ex-Feyenoord boss confirmed the Croatian has expressed a desire to leave St Mary's.

'There are a lot of rumours,' explained Koeman. 'He said he would like to go, we will wait for the bid, but if there is no bid we will continue. I know the situation.'

